<div class="help-block mt-5 mb-5">
    <h1 class="mb-3">Kickstart: Feature Documentation</h1>
    <div class="kickstart-features ml-6 mb-5">
        <h2 class="mt-5 mb-3">Kickstart</h2>

        <div class="kickstart-block ml-5 mb-5">
            <p>The Kickstart feature serves as a central platform for managing course layout views and templates, providing users with easy access to essential resources and tools, along with filtering, sorting, and search options.<br>
            The kickstart serves as an interface page that provides access to various Kickstart functionalities, including:</p>

            <h3 class="mt-5 mb-3">Kickstart Features</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Course Templates</li>
                <li>Course Library (Pro)</li>
                <li>Help Documentation</li>
                <li>Student View</li>
                <li>Create Template from Course (Pro)</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="kickstart-features ml-6 mb-5 pl-5">
        <h2 class="mb-3">1. Course Template</h2>
        <p class="ml-6">Course Templates are pre-built course structures designed to simplify the setup of new courses. The Course Templates feature displays a list or grid of available templates, allowing users to easily browse, search, and select the desired template.<br>
        A <b>Manage Templates</b> button is available to users with management permissions, providing quick access to create and manage templates efficiently. This feature streamlines course setup by offering ready-made templates and flexible management options.</p>

        <h2 class="mt-5 mb-3 pl-5">Course Templates features</h2>
        <ul class="ml-4">
            <li class="mb-2">The Search feature allows users to find specific templates by entering keywords related to the template's name, tags, or description. This functionality helps users quickly locate the desired template from the list of available options.</li>
            <li class="mb-2">Layout The Course Templates feature displays available templates in a list or grid view, enabling users to quickly find and select the desired template. It includes a search function to make template discovery easy and efficient.</li>
            <li class="mb-2">The Manage Templates button is available to users with template management permissions. It provides quick access to create, edit, and manage course templates efficiently. This feature allows administrators and authorized users to maintain and organize templates, ensuring that relevant and up-to-date templates are available for course creation.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="mt-5 mb-3 pl-5">How to Use Course Templates</h3>
        <ol class="ml-4">
            <li class="mb-2">Navigate to the course view page.</li>
            <li class="mb-2">Click <b>Kickstart</b> in the secondary navigation menu.</li>
            <li class="mb-2">Select <b>Course Templates</b> from the Kickstart options.</li>
            <li class="mb-2">Browse the available templates displayed in a list or grid view.</li>
            <li class="mb-2">Use the search bar to quickly find specific templates by name, tags, or description.</li>
            <li class="mb-2">If you have management permissions, click <b>Manage Templates</b> to create, edit, or organize templates as needed.</li>
        </ol>
    </div>

    <div class="kickstart-features ml-6 mb-5 pl-5">
        <h2 class="mb-3">2. Course Library (Pro)</h2>
        <p class="ml-6">The Course Library provides a collection of available courses that users can easily import. It includes powerful search, sorting, and filtering options to help users quickly find relevant courses.<br>
        The library's header features a search bar for fast course discovery. When custom field filters are applied, the course list updates accordingly to display only the most relevant results.<br>
        Each course element displays important details, including the course title, category path, course start date, course ID number, and tags, giving users the information they need to select the right course efficiently.</p>

        <h3 class="mt-5 pl-5">Purpose of the Course Library</h3>
        <h5 class="mt-4 mb-3 pl-5">The Course Library helps users:</h5>
        <ul class="ml-4">
            <li class="mb-2">Import Courses Easily: Quickly bring in existing courses without creating new ones from scratch.</li>
            <li class="mb-2">Find Courses Fast: Use search, sorting, and filtering tools to locate the right course quickly.</li>
            <li class="mb-2">Get Important Details: See course information like title, category, start date, ID number, and tags to make informed choices.</li>
            <li class="mb-2">Customize Searches: Filter courses using custom fields to find the most relevant options.</li>
            <li class="mb-2">Save Time: Simplify the course selection process and reuse well-structured courses efficiently.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="mt-5 mb-3 pl-5">How to Use the Course Library</h3>
        <ol class="ml-4">
            <li class="mb-2">Navigate to the course view page.</li>
            <li class="mb-2">Click <b>Kickstart</b> in the secondary navigation menu.</li>
            <li class="mb-2">Select <b>Course Library</b> from the Kickstart options.</li>
            <li class="mb-2">Use the search bar, sorting, and filtering options to find the desired course.</li>
            <li class="mb-2">Click <b>Import Course</b> to import a specific course.</li>
            <li class="mb-2">Use the <b>Show Contents</b> button to view the sections within a course before importing.</li>
        </ol>
    </div>

    <div class="kickstart-features ml-6 mb-5 pl-5">
        <h2 class="mb-3">3. Student View Feature</h2>
        <p class="ml-6">The <b>Student View</b> feature allows both students and instructors to preview the given instructions in the Kickstart settings of a course as they appear to students, without access to management capabilities.</p>

        <ul class="ml-4">
            <li class="mb-2">If the course format is not set to <b>Kickstart</b>, the <b>Student View</b> feature will be unavailable for students. In this case, instructors will receive a warning message indicating that <b>Student View</b> is not supported.
            <li class="mb-2">If the course is set to the <b>Kickstart</b> format, both students and instructors can access the <b>Student View</b> and review the instructions on the course page as specified in the course format settings.
        </ul>

        <p class="ml-6">This feature ensures that users can accurately experience the course from a student’s perspective, facilitating a better understanding of the learning environment.</p>

        <h3 class="mt-5 pl-5 mb-3">Purpose</h3>
        <ul class="ml-4">
            <li class="mb-2">For Instructors: Helps verify course content, layout, and instructional materials from a student’s perspective, ensuring clarity and usability.</li>
            <li class="mb-2">For Students: Provides a structured view of course instructions and materials, as specified in the course format settings.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="mt-5 pl-5 mb-3">How to Use Student View</h3>
        <ol class="ml-4">
            <li class="mb-2">Navigate to the Course View page.</li>
            <li class="mb-2">Click <b>Kickstart</b> in the secondary navigation menu (this option is not available for student users).</li>
            <li class="mb-2">If the course format is Kickstart, all users can preview the course as it appears to students.</li>
            <li class="mb-2">If the course format is not Kickstart, a warning message will indicate that the Student View feature is unavailable for non-Kickstart formats.</li>
        </ol>
    </div>

    <div class="kickstart-features ml-6 mb-5 pl-5">
        <h2 class="mb-3">4. Create Template from Course (Pro)</h2>

        <p class="ml-6">The <b>Create Template from Course</b> feature provides a simple and efficient way to generate a reusable template from an existing course.
         This functionality enables administrators and authorized users to streamline course creation by preserving the structure, content, and settings of a course for future use. A template creation form will appear the first time you use this feature.<br></p>

        <h3 class="mt-5 pl-5 mb-3">Purpose</h3>
        <ul class="ml-4">
            <li class="mb-2">Create reusable templates from well-structured courses.</li>
            <li class="mb-2">Promote consistent course design across multiple courses.</li>
            <li class="mb-2">Enable easy sharing of course formats within the organization.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="mt-5 pl-5">How to Use Create Template from Course</h3>
        <ol class="ml-4">
            <li class="mb-2">Navigate to the course view page.</li>
            <li class="mb-2">Click <b>Kickstart</b> in the secondary navigation menu.</li>
            <li class="mb-2">Select <b>Create Template</b> from Course from the Kickstart options.</li>
            <li class="mb-2">When an authorized user selects the <b>Create Template from Course</b> option within an active course, a template creation form appears.</li>
            <li class="mb-2">The user provides necessary details and confirms the template creation.</li>
            <li class="mb-2">Once created, the template is added to the template list, making it accessible for future course development.</li>
        </ol>
        <h3 class="mt-5 pl-5">Summary</h3>
        <p class="ml-6">The Kickstart project offers a comprehensive set of tools for course setup and management, enhancing efficiency and consistency in course delivery. By centralizing these features under a single menu item, the platform ensures a user-friendly experience for instructors and administrators.</p>
    </div>
</div>

